    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-05-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <head>198. Record of Actions and Decisions Taken at a Meeting in Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>’ Office, Department of State,
                    Washington, May 17, 1957<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d198fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 600.0012/5–1757. Secret. Prepared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_GJNJ1">Greene</persName>. For a summary of this
                        meeting, see <ref target="#d197">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>. A footnote to the source text reads: “<gloss target="#t_IO1"
                            >IO</gloss>—Messrs. Owsley and <persName corresp="#p_BV1"
                            >Baker</persName> are preparing a summary record of the meeting.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1957</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follows a list of participants which is identical to the one printed <ref
                        target="#d197">
                        <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                    </ref>.]</p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Governor <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName>’s Disarmament
                        Proposals</item>
                </list>
                <p>The following are actions and decisions of the meeting:</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> and his staff are to re-cast
                    his May 9 proposals<note n="2" xml:id="d198fn2">See <ref target="#d195">Document
                            195</ref>.</note> along the lines of an international document to show
                    what it would look like if it were to be negotiated and thus eliminating many of
                    the purely American domestic short cuts in it. In this process they will: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">in paragraph 2</hi>: Elaborate the concept of
                            manufacture and use of nuclear weapons before and/or during
                            hostilities.</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">in Paragraph 4</hi>: Specify that re-fabrication of
                            existing weapons is not excluded and re-arrange the order of the
                            developments to make clear that an inspection system must be designed
                            and installed first.</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">in Paragraph 12</hi>: Make clear that paragraph 12
                            applies to both nuclear and conventional armaments.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0554" n="526" xml:id="pg_526"/>
                <p>Admiral Strauss will promptly consult with Governor <persName corresp="#p_SHE1"
                        >Stassen</persName> on the restricted data<note n="3" xml:id="d198fn3">The
                        word “data” is inserted in handwriting on the source text.</note>
                    implications of some of the latter’s proposals and thereafter formulate the
                        <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss> position on those proposals by May
                    22.</p>
                <p>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_WCE1">Wilson</persName> will get the <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> and Defense comments on the first 18 paragraphs
                    (and executing provisions of the last paragraphs) of the <persName
                        corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> proposals ready by the middle or end of
                    next week but will not attempt detailed analysis of the latter phases of the
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> proposals which are largely
                    designed for political purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">JG</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
